The famous quote "I am no bird; and no net ensnares me: I am a free human being with an independent will; which I now exert to leave you" appears in Charlotte Brontë's *Jane Eyre*. This scene showcases Jane finally releasing years of being treated like a thing, an object without feeling, and declaring her independence and fierceness of character.
